Obiect: But how can a man wander from God,Ob: or loſe him? Whereſoeuer I am, God is there preſent; he filleth both heauen and earth;
Ier. 23.24. Pſal. 27. Pſal. 139.2.3.4 he is with me at my ſitting, riſing, lying downe, in the thoughts of my heart, words of my tongue, wayes of my feete, nay, in my reines, and bones. His preſence cannot be auoided, who ſitteth on the Circle of heauen,1 Reg. 8.27. Iſa. 66.1. 
and beholdeth the inhabitants of the earth as Graſhoppers, whoſe throne is the heauen of heauens, and the earth is his footeſtoole, and his wayes are in the great deepe, &c.
